 View this email as Webpage (http://tsxventurenews.net/view.php/697733/657616)Hodgins Concludes Spring 2010 Marathon of Auctions&nbsp;Hodgins Auctioneers Inc. (HA-TSX.V) (&#8220;Hodgins&#8221; or the &#8220;Company&#8221;) is pleased to announce the completion of 25 auctions in the last 29 business days.&nbsp;Leading off the spring auction season was a major online equipment auction and a Northern Alberta real estate auction.&nbsp; The online auction featured 256 lots of farm and industrial equipment, and had 472 registered bidders.&nbsp;The live Northern Alberta real estate auction was conducted March 29, 2010.&nbsp; It consisted of 630 acres of land divided into ten parcels.&nbsp; The total selling price was $887,000 including buildings.&nbsp; The raw farmland averaged $812 per acre.&nbsp;The Spring Auction season concluded with an interesting auction of farm equipment, antiques and collectibles.&nbsp; 948 lots were sold at a Prince Albert, Saskatchewan auction, on May 1, 2010.&nbsp; 749 buyers registered to bid live and online; from more than nine provinces and states. Other auctions in the Spring Marathon included a combination of industrial, agricultural and commercial auctions.&nbsp; They spanned the provinces of Alberta, Saskatchewan and Manitoba, and were a mixture of live onsite auctions, exclusively online auctions and hybrid live/online auctions.&nbsp;Barrie Jung, president of Hodgins Auctioneers Inc., stated, &#8220;Strong demand for equipment translated into large buyer audiences this spring.&nbsp; Also, we were especially pleased with the growth of online participation from both buyers and sellers.&#8221;&nbsp;About Hodgins Auctioneers Inc.&nbsp;Headquartered in Melfort, Saskatchewan for more than 50 years, Hodgins is a provider of professional auction services.&nbsp; Hodgins is renowned for its experienced auctioneers, award-winning promotions, dependable results and commitment to providing the ultimate marketplace for the sale of assets by auction.&n